aming]]}}\n| {{hlist|[[RBC Records|RBC]]|[[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]}}\n| <ref name=\"autogenerated2\">{{cite web|url=https://music.apple.com/gb/album/poppin-feat-lil-pump-smokepurpp-single/1502185528|title=Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) - Single by KSI|last=|first=|date=27 March 2020|website=iTunes|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=11 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|3}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GGLE8gk9fng Audio video] on [[YouTube]]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xa0qshcRhDQ Music video] on [[YouTube]]\n*[https://genius.com/Ksi-poppin-lyrics Lyrics of the song] at [[Genius (website)|Genius]]\n\n{{KSI}}\n{{Lil Pump}}\n\n[[Category:2020 songs]]\n[[Category:2020 singles]]\n[[Category:BMG Rights Management singles]]\n[[Category:KSI (entertainer) songs]]\n[[Category:Lil Pump songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by KSI]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Lil Pump]]\n[[Category:YouTube music videos]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2020 single by KSI featuring Lil Pump and Smokepurpp}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox song\n|name=Poppin\n|cover=KSI Poppin Cover.jpeg\n|alt=\n|type=single\n|artist=[[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] featuring [[Lil Pump]] and [[Smokepurpp]]\n|album=Dissimulation|released=27 March 2020\n|format=\n* [[Music download|Digital download]]\n* [[Streaming media|streaming]]\n|recorded=2020\n|studio=\n|genre=[[Hip hop]]\n|length=3:33\n|label=\n* [[RBC Records|RBC]]\n* [[BMG Rights Management|BMG]]\n|writer=\n* [[KSI (entertainer)|Olajide Olatunji]]\n* [[Lil Pump|Gazzy Garcia]]\n* [[Smokepurpp|Omar Pineiro]]\n* Diego Avendano\n* Kevin Price\n* Jamal Rashid<ref name=autogenerated1>{{cite web |title=Poppin by KSI featuring Lil Pump & Smokepurpp |url=https://listen.tidal.com/album/133831942/credits |website=Tidal |accessdate=27 March 2020}}</ref>\n|producer=* Diego Ave\n* Go Grizzly\n* Mally Mall<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n|chronology=[[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]]\n|prev_title=[[Wake Up Call (KSI song)|Wake Up Call]]\n|prev_year=2020\n|next_title=Houdini\n|next_year=2020\n|misc={{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Lil Pump]]\n | type       = Singles\n | prev_title = You Know You Lit\n | prev_year  = 2020\n | title      = Poppin\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}\n{{Extra chronology\n | artist     = [[Smokepurpp]]\n | type       = singles\n | prev_title = RR\n | prev_year  = 2020\n | title      = Poppin\n | year       = 2020\n | next_title = \n | next_year  = \n}}}}\n\"'''Poppin'''\" is a song by British YouTube personality and rapper [[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]], featuring American rappers [[Lil Pump]] and [[Smokepurpp]]. The song is produced by American producers Diego Ave, Go Grizzly and Mally Mall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hotnewhiphop.com/ksi-unites-with-lil-pump-and-smokepurpp-on-gaudy-poppin-new-song.1986685.html|title=KSI Unites With Lil Pump & Smokepurpp On Gaudy \"Poppin\"|website=HotNewHipHop|language=en|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> It was released on 27 March 2020 through [[RBC Records]], under [[BMG Rights Management]].<ref name=\"ein2\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.einnews.com/pr_news/512477940/ksi-to-release-new-single-poppin-featuring-lil-pump-smokepurpp-on-march-27th|title=KSI to Release New Single, \u201cPoppin\u201d Featuring Lil Pump, Smokepurpp on March 27th|date=23 March 2020|publisher=EIN News}}</ref> It is the third single from KSI's upcoming 2020 debut album ''Dissimulation''. The song charted at number 43 on the [[UK Singles Chart]].<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/singles-chart/20200403/7501/|title=Official Singles Chart Top 100 {{!}} Official Charts Company|last=|first=|date=|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref>\n\n== Promotion ==\nOn 18 March 2020, KSI announced via social media that he would be releasing a new single in the next week, and on the same day, he posted the song's artwork to his social media pages, revealing that the song is titled \"Poppin\" and that it features Lil Pump and Smokepurpp.<ref>{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=1240310548371255297|title=New single coming out next week. Clue of the song name and feature here https://K-S-I.lnk.to/search/spotify|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref><ref>{{Cite tweet|user=KSIOlajidebt|number=1240344439651995654|title=https://ksi.ffm.to/poppin\u00a0 Out next week lmao. Pre order/pre save nowpic.twitter.com/ZjO6pXx2ZG|date=2020-03-18|access-date=2020-03-23}}</ref> The song was made available for [[pre-order]] on the same day.<ref name=\"ein2\"/>\n\n=== \"Poppin challenge\" ===\nOn 30 March 2020, KSI announced via social media that he would be hosting a competition called \"#PoppinChallenge\". He asked people to record and submit their own verses for \"Poppin\", and the best verse, decided by public vote, will replace Lil Pump's verse on a remix of the song which will appear on the deluxe edition of KSI's upcoming 2020 album ''Dissimulation''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/KSIOlajidebt/status/1244735326179950593|title=Got a big one for you  #poppinchallengepic.twitter.com/NWe2Lq74Gq|last=KSI|date=2020-03-30|website=@KSIOlajidebt|language=en|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> On 17 April 2020, American YouTube rapper Crypt was announced as the winner of the competition.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=oMIRi2eTgb0|title=The Winner Of The Poppin Challenge Is...|last=|first=|date=17 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QOCY2QC7AWY|title=I WON THE KSI POPPIN' CHALLENGE|last=|first=|date=17 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=17 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Commercial performance ==\nThe song entered the UK Singles Chart at number 43.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/artist/48106/ksi/|title=KSI {{!}} full Official Chart History {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|access-date=2020-04-17}}</ref> It dropped to number 56 the following week, before dropping out of the top 100.<ref name=\":1\" /> The song debuted at number 23 on the [[UK R&B Singles and Albums Charts|UK R&B Singles Chart]] and spent a total of two weeks on the chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.officialcharts.com/charts/r-and-b-singles-chart/20200410/114/|title=Official R&B Singles Chart Top 40 {{!}} Official Charts Company|website=www.officialcharts.com|language=en|access-date=2020-04-20}}</ref>\n\n== Music video ==\nAn audio visualiser video for the song was uploaded to KSI's [[YouTube]] channel on 26 March 2020. As of April 2020, it has 6 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GGLE8gk9fng|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp)|date=26 March 2020|via=[[YouTube]]|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref> The music video, directed by TajvsJaj, was filmed in [[Los Angeles]] in March 2020 and was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 3 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://grmdaily.com/video/ksi-poppin-lil-pump-smokepurpp|title=KSI Gives Visual Treatment To \"Poppin\" Featuring Lil Pump & Smokepurpp|last=|first=|date=3 April 2020|website=[[GRM Daily]]|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-04-10}}</ref> The music video stars Asian dancer Bailey Sok and features cameo appearances from American actor and comedian [[King Bach]] and two of the song's producers, Diego Ave and Mally Mall.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://grungecake.com/ksi-popping-lil-pump-smokepurpp/articles/65556|title=English rapper KSI enlists Lil Pump and Smokepurpp for 'Poppin': Watch|date=2020-04-06|website=GRUNGECAKE|language=en-GB|access-date=2020-04-07}}</ref> As of April 2020, it has 7 million views.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=xa0qshcRhDQ|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Official Music Video]|last=|first=|date=3 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=7 April 2020}}</ref> A [[Making-of|behind-the-scenes]] video of the filming of the music video was uploaded to KSI's YouTube channel on 10 April 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fmf_KsHjGC8|title=KSI - Poppin (feat. Lil Pump & Smokepurpp) [Behind The Scenes]|last=|first=|date=10 April 2020|website=YouTube|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Track listing==\n{{Track listing\n| headline = Digital download<ref name=autogenerated2 />\n| title1 = Poppin\n| note1 = featuring [[Lil Pump]] and [[Smokepurpp]]\n| length1 = 3:33\n| length6 = \n| length10 = \n| title10 = \n| length9 = \n| title9 = \n| length8 = \n| title8 = \n| length7 = \n| title7 = \n| length5 = \n| title6 = \n| title5 = \n| length4 = \n| title4 = \n| length3 = \n| title3 = \n| length2 = \n| title2 = \n| all_writing = \n| total_length = \n}}\n\n== Credits and personnel ==\nCredits adapted from [[Tidal (service)|Tidal]].<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n{{div col}}\n*[[KSI (entertainer)|KSI]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*[[Lil Pump]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*[[Smokepurpp]] \u2013 vocals, songwriter\n*Diego Ave \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Go Grizzly \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Mally Mall \u2013 producer, songwriter\n*Henkka Niemist\u00f6 \u2013 engineer\n*Michalis Michael \u2013 engineer\n{{div col end}}\n\n== Charts ==\n[[Category:Singlechart usages for UKrandb]]\n[[Category:Singlechart called without artist]]\n[[Category:Singlechart called without song]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" | Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\" | Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | Ireland ([[Irish Recorded Music Association|IRMA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://irma.ie/index.cfm?page=irish-charts&chart=Singles|title=IRMA \u2013 Irish C