AQBAJ&pg=PA51 |date=2015 |publisher=Lancer Publishers |ISBN=978-81-7062-301-4 |pages=51\u2013 |ref={{sfnref|Cheema, Crimson Chinar|2015}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Dasgupta |first=C. |authorlink=Chandrashekhar Dasgupta |title=War and Diplomacy in Kashmir, 1947\u201348 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=jEtuAAAAMAAJ |date=2014 |origyear=first published 2002 |publisher=SAGE Publications |isbn=978-81-321-1795-7 |ref={{sfnref|Dasgupta, War and Diplomacy in Kashmir|2014}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Effendi |first=Col. M. Y. |title=Punjab Cavalry: Evolution, Role, Organisation and Tactical Doctrine 11 Cavalry, Frontier Force, 1849-1971 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MeXeAAAAMAAJ |year=2007 |publisher=Oxford University Press |location=Karachi |ISBN=978-0-19-547203-5 |ref={{sfnref|Effendi, Punjab Cavalry|2007}}}}\n* {{citation |first=Ramachandra |last=Guha |authorlink=Ramachandra Guha |title=India after Gandhi: The History of the World's Largest Democracy |publisher=Pan Macmillan |year=2008 |ISBN=0330396110 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=29lXtwoeA44C |ref={{sfnref|Guha, India after Gandhi|2008}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Hajari |first=Nisid |authorlink=Nisid Hajari |title=Midnight's Furies: The Deadly Legacy of India's Partition |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OJGdBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA185 |year=2015 |publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt |isbn=978-0-547-66924-3 |pages=185\u2013 |ref={{sfnref|Hajari, Midnight's Furies|2015}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Hiro |first=Dilip |title=The Longest August: The Unflinching Rivalry Between India and Pakistan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PpPCBAAAQBAJ |date=2015 |publisher=Nation Books |ISBN=978-1-56858-503-1 |ref={{sfnref|Hiro, Longest August|2015}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Jamal |first=Arif |title=Shadow War: The Untold Story of Jihad in Kashmir |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=TNO5MAAACAAJ |year=2009 |publisher=Melville House |isbn=978-1-933633-59-6 |ref={{sfnref|Jamal, Shadow War|2009}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Joshi |first=Manoj |title=Kashmir, 1947-1965: A Story Retold |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=uAT3oENcxDgC |year=2008 |publisher=India Research Press |isbn=978-81-87943-52-5 |ref={{sfnref|Joshi, Kashmir, 1947-1965: A Story Retold|2008}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Hodson |first=H. V. |title=The Great Divide: Britain, India, Pakistan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MC2UoAEACAAJ |year=1969 |publisher=Hutchinson |location=London |ref={{sfnref|Hodson, The Great Divide|1969}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Korbel |first=Josef |authorlink=Josef Korbel |title=Danger in Kashmir |publisher=Princeton University Press |edition=second |year=1966 |origyear=first published 1954 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=7Q7WCgAAQBAJ |ref={{sfnref|Korbel, Danger in Kashmir|1966}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Mahajan |first=Mehr Chand |authorlink=Mehr Chand Mahajan |title=Looking Back: The Autobiography of Mehr Chand Mahajan, Former Chief Justice of India |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=AW5u9QSxCFwC |year=1963 |publisher=Asia Publishing House |ref={{sfnref|Mahajan, Looking Back|1963}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Moore |first=Robin James |title=Making the new Commonwealth |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=b_l-AAAAIAAJ |year=1987 |publisher=Clarendon Press |ISBN=978-0-19-820112-0 |ref={{sfnref|Moore, Making the new Commonwealth|1987}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Palit |first=D. K. |title=Jammu and Kashmir Arms: History of the J & K Rifles |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KGZDnzqQj2QC |year=1972 |publisher=Palit & Dutt |ref={{sfnref|Palit, Jammu and Kashmir Arms|1972}}}}\n* {{citation |last1=Prasad |first1=Sri Nandan |last2=Pal |first2=Dharm |title=Operations in Jammu & Kashmir, 1947\u201348 |url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.116302 |year=1987 |publisher=History Division, Ministry of Defence, Government of India |ref={{sfnref|Prasad & Pal, Operations in Jammu & Kashmir |1987}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Raghavan |first=Srinath |title=War and Peace in Modern India |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EbtBJb1bsHUC&pg=PA101 |date=2010 |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan |ISBN=978-1-137-00737-7 |pages=101\u2013 |ref={{sfnref|Raghavan, War and Peace in Modern India|2010}}}}\n* {{citation |first=Shuja |last=Nawaz |title=The First Kashmir War Revisited |journal=India Review |volume=7 |number=2 |pp=115\u2013154 |DOI=10.1080/14736480802055455 |date=May 2008  |ref={{sfnref|Nawaz, The First Kashmir War Revisited|2008}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Sarila |first=Narendra Singh |title=The Shadow of the Great Game: The Untold Story of India's Partition |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WW5FPgAACAAJ |year=2007 |publisher=Constable |isbn=978-1-84529-588-2 |ref={{sfnref|Sarila, The Shadow of the Great Game|2007}}}}\n* {{citation |first=Victoria |last=Schofield |authorlink=Victoria Schofield |title=Kashmir in Conflict |publisher=I. B. Taurus & Co |location=London and New York |year=2003 |origyear=First published in 2000 |ISBN=1860648983 |ref={{sfnref|Schofield, Kashmir in Conflict|2003}} |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/00book584554548 }}\n* {{citation |first=Christopher |last=Snedden |authorlink=Christopher Snedden |title=Kashmir: The Unwritten History |publisher=HarperCollins India |year=2013 |ISBN=9350298988 |origyear=first published as ''The Untold Story of the People of Azad Kashmir'', 2012 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0cPjAAAAQBAJ |ref={{sfnref|Snedden, Kashmir: The Unwritten History|2013}}}}\n* {{citation |last=Zaheer |first=Hasan |title=The Times and Trial of the Rawalpindi Conspiracy, 1951: The First Coup Attempt in Pakistan |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rjNuAAAAMAAJ |year=1998 |publisher=Oxford University Press |ISBN=978-0-19-577892-2 |ref={{sfnref|Zaheer, The Times and Trial of the Rawalpindi Conspiracy|1998}}}}\n\n==Further reading==\n;Major sources:\n* {{aut|Ministry of Defence,  Government of India}}. ''Operations in Jammu and Kashmir 1947\u20131948''. (1987). Thomson Press (India) Limited, New Delhi. This is the Indian Official History.\n* {{aut|Lamb, Alastair}}. ''Kashmir: A Disputed Legacy, 1846\u20131990''. (1991). Roxford Books. {{ISBN|0-907129-06-4}}.\n* {{aut|Praval, K.C.}} ''The Indian Army After Independence''. (1993). Lancer International, {{ISBN|1-897829-45-0}}\n* {{aut|Sen, Maj Gen L.P.}} ''Slender Was The Thread: The Kashmir confrontation 1947\u20131948.'' (1969). Orient Longmans Ltd, New Delhi.\n* {{aut|Vas, Lt Gen. E. A.}} ''Without Baggage:  A personal account of the Jammu and Kashmir Operations 1947\u20131949''. (1987). Natraj Publishers Dehradun. {{ISBN|81-85019-09-6}}.\n\n;Other sources:\n* {{aut|Cohen, Lt Col Maurice}}. ''Thunder over Kashmir''. (1955). Orient Longman Ltd. Hyderabad\n* {{aut|Hinds, Brig Gen SR}}. ''Battle of Zoji La''. (1962). Military Digest, New Delhi.\n* {{aut|Sandhu, Maj Gen Gurcharan}}. ''The Indian Armour:  History Of The Indian Armoured Corps 1941\u20131971''. (1987). Vision Books Private Limited, New Delhi,  {{ISBN|81-7094-004-4}}.\n* {{aut|Singh, Maj K Brahma}}. ''History of Jammu and Kashmir Rifles (1820\u20131956)''. (1990). Lancer International New Delhi, {{ISBN|81-7062-091-0}}.\n* Ayub, Muhammad (2005). An army, Its Role and Rule: A History of the Pakistan Army from Independence to Kargil, 1947\u20131999. RoseDog Books. {{ISBN|9780805995947}}.\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110405210142/http://indianarmy.nic.in/Site/FormTemplete/frmTempSimple.aspx?MnId=BfMpdR9l1kE=&ParentID=a2GSpnDbruI= Partition and Indo Pak War of 1947\u201348], Indian Army, archived 5 April 2011.\n\n{{Kashmir conflict}}\n{{Military of India}}\n{{Military of Pakistan}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Indo-Pakistani War Of 1947}}\n[[Category:Indo-Pakistani wars]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1947]]\n[[Category:Wars involving India]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1948]]\n[[Category:Conflicts in 1949]]\n[[Category:History of Azad Kashmir]]\n[[Category:History of Jammu and Kashmir]]\n[[Category:Military history of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:History of Pakistan]]\n[[Category:Kashmir conflict|1947]]\n[[Category:1947 in India]]\n[[Category:1948 in India]]\n[[Category:1949 in India]]\n[[Category:Government of Liaquat Ali Khan]]\n[[Category:Nehru administration]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1947\u20131948 war between India and Pakistan}}\n{{Use British English|date=March 2013}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2019}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict    = Indo-Pakistani War of 1947\u20131948\n| partof      = the [[Indo-Pakistani wars and conflicts]]\n| campaign    = \n| colour_scheme = background:#91ACDA\n| image       = Indian soldiers fighting in 1947 war.jpg\n| caption     = Indian soldiers during the 1947\u20131948 war\n| notes       = Conflict started when [[Pashtun people|Pashtun]] tribal forces from Pakistan invaded the [[princely state]] of [[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Kashmir and Jammu]], prompting Indian and Pakistani armies to get involved.\n| date        = 22 October 1947&nbsp;\u2013 5 January 1949<br>({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=10|day1=22|year1=1947|month2=1|day2=5|year2=1949}})\n| place       = [[Kashmir]]\n| result      = [[Line of Control|Ceasefire agreement]]\n* [[Jammu and Kashmir (princely state)|Princely state of Jammu and Kashmir]] [[Instrument of Accession (Jammu and Kashmir)|acceded]] to India\n* UN Ceasefire Line of 1949 (later becomes [[Line of Control]] after the [[Simla Agreement]] of 1972)\n| territory   = Pakistan controls roughly a third of {{nowrap|Kashmir ([[Azad Kashmir]] and [[Gilgit-Baltistan]]),}} whereas India controls the rest ([[Kashmir Valley]], [[Jammu]] and [[Ladakh]]).<ref>{{Cite web  |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/hi/english/static/in_depth/south_asia/2002/india_pakistan/timeline/1947_48.stm |title=BBC on the 1947\u201348 war |access-date=30 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150130232421/http://news.bbc.co.uk/hi/english/static/in_depth/south_asia/2002/india_pakistan/timeline/1947_48.stm |archive-date=30 January 2015 |url-status=live  }}<